label.value: inviable elongated mononucleate cell with cell cycle arrest at mitotic G2/M phase transition

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a cell is inviable, is longer than normal, has one nucleus, and the mitotic cell cycle is arrested with nuclei at the mitotic G2/M phase transition.

label.value: inviable elongated cell with cell cycle arrest at mitotic G2/M phase transition

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a cell is inviable, is longer than normal, and the mitotic cell cycle is arrested with nuclei at the mitotic G2/M phase transition.

label.value: abolished protein localization to lateral cell cortex during glucose starvation

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to the cell cortex does not occur when the cell is subject to glucose starvation.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased protein localization to lateral cell cortex during glucose starvation

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to the cell cortex is decreased when the cell is subject to glucose starvation.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal protein localization to lateral cell cortex during glucose starvation

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to the cell cortex is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) when the cell is subject to glucose starvation.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased microtubule depolymerization at cell side

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the removal of tubulin dimers from a microtubule occurs to a lower extent than normal in the lateral part of the cell.

label.value: decreased GTPase activator activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the activity of a GTPase activator is decreased.

label.value: normal dynamic protein localization to cell tip

value.value: A cell phenotype in which a protein that is normally dynamically localized to one or both cell tips shows a normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) temporal pattern of localization. For example, a protein may move from one cell tip to the other at a normal frequency and amplitude.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased protein localization to cell cortex of non-growing cell tip

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the cell cortex of a non-growing cell tip is decreased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased number of Ssb1 foci

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the number of sites at which the protein Ssb1 accumulates is lower than normal.

label.value: normal number of Ssb1 foci

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the number of sites at which the protein Ssb1 accumulates normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: mitochondria absent from cell

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the cell does not contain any detectable mitochondria.

label.value: large ERMES foci present in decreased numbers

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a cell contains fewer, but larger, ERMES foci than normal. An ERMES focus is a site that contains one or more ERMES complex(es).

label.value: decreased mitochondrial phosphatidylethanolamine level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of phosphatidylethanolamine measured in the mitochondrion differs from normal.

label.value: decreased mitochondrial phosphatidylserine level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of phosphatidylserine measured in the mitochondrion differs from normal.

label.value: resistance to tebuconazole

value.value: An increased chemical resistance phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells grow in the presence of a higher concentration of tebuconazole than normal.

label.value: sensitive to potassium nitrate

value.value: A phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to potassium chloride. Cells stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of potassium nitrate that allows wild type cells to grow.

label.value: abnormal SMN complex assembly

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which SMN complex assembly is abnormal.

label.value: abolished SMN complex assembly

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which SMN complex assembly is abolished.

label.value: decreased SMN complex assembly

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the occurrence of SMN complex assembly is decreased.

label.value: abnormal protein recycling from late endosome to Golgi

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the movement of proteins via vesicles from late endosomes to the Golgi is abnormal. This process is normally mediated by the retromer complex.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased nucleosome-dependent ATPase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of nucleosome-dependent ATPase activity is decreased.

label.value: normal cellular physical quality phenotype

value.value: A phenotype in which a physical object quality, such as morphology, number, location, etc., of a cell or a cellular component is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: normal ERMES foci

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the ERMES foci in a cell are normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) in number, size, and distribution. An ERMES focus is a site that contains one or more ERMES complex(es).

label.value: normal protein localization to late endosome

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to late endosomes is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased cell population growth on phenylalanine nitrogen source

value.value: A vegetative cell population growth phenotype in which cell growth is decreased relative to normal in a medium containing L-phenylalanine as the nitrogen source.

label.value: abnormal late endosome morphology

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the size, shape, or structure of late endosomes is abnormal.

label.value: normal protein kinase activity during cellular response to osmotic stress

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of a protein kinase activity is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) during a cellular response to osmotic stress.

label.value: decreased protein localization to mitotic spindle during anaphase

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the mitotic spindle is decreased during anaphase.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal protein distribution along RNA polymerase II-transcribed genes during mitotic metaphase

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the distribution of a protein localized to chromatin along the length of genes that can be transcribed by RNA polymerase II is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) during metaphase of the mitotic cell cycle.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal protein localization to chromatin at 3' end of genes

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the distribution of a protein localized to chromatin at the 3' ends of genes is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal protein localization to chromatin at 3' end of RNA polymerase III-transcribed genes during mitotic metaphase

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the distribution of a protein localized to chromatin at the 3' ends of genes that can be transcribed by RNA polymerase III is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) during metaphase of the mitotic cell cycle.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abnormal protein localization to chromatin at 3' end of genes

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the distribution of a protein localized to chromatin at the 3' ends of genes is abnormal.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased protein localization to chromatin at 3' end of RNA polymerase III-transcribed genes

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the distribution of a protein localized to chromatin at the 3' ends of genes that can be transcribed by RNA polymerase III is increased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased protein localization to chromatin at 3' end of RNA polymerase III-transcribed genes during mitotic metaphase

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the distribution of a protein localized to chromatin at the 3' ends of genes that can be transcribed by RNA polymerase III is increased during metaphase of the mitotic cell cycle.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: protein displaced from 3' end to 5' end of RNA polymerase II-transcribed genes during mitotic metaphase

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the distribution of a protein localized to chromatin along the length of genes that can be transcribed by RNA polymerase II is altered such that more of the protein is present at the 5' end, and less at the 3' end, than normal during metaphase of the mitotic cell cycle.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased mitochondrial membrane potential

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype in which the mitochondrial membrane potential, i.e. the electric potential existing across the mitochondrial membrane, is greater than normal.

label.value: normal protein localization to chromatin at 3' end of RNA polymerase II-transcribed genes during mitotic metaphase

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the distribution of a protein localized to chromatin at the 3' ends of genes that can be transcribed by RNA polymerase II is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) during metaphase of the mitotic cell cycle.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: delayed onset of nucleolar ring disassembly

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which nucleolar ring disassembly begins later than normal. Nucleolar rings are structures located at the nucleolar periphery where several nuclear factors are reversibly aggregated and sequestered during acute heat stress. They normally disassemble upon removal of heat stress.

label.value: normal nucleolar ring assembly

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which nucleolar ring assembly is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). Nucleolar rings are structures located at the nucleolar periphery where several nuclear factors are reversibly aggregated and sequestered during acute heat stress.

label.value: abnormal protein distribution along RNA polymerase II-transcribed genes during mitotic metaphase

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the distribution of a protein localized to chromatin along the length of genes that can be transcribed by RNA polymerase II is abnormal during metaphase of the mitotic cell cycle.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: premature actomyosin contractile ring assembly during mitotic interphase

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which actomyosin contractile ring assembly begins during interphase of the mitotic cell cycle. Contractile ring assembly normally begins during M phase.

label.value: premature septum assembly during mitotic interphase

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which septum assembly begins during interphase of the mitotic cell cycle. Septum assembly normally begins during M phase.

label.value: spindle collapse during meiotic prophase I

value.value: A cell phenotype in which a short spindle assembles during the first meiotic nuclear division, and may begin elongation, but does not elongate normally or completely, and collapses during prophase I. Upon collapse the spindle may break or shrink.

label.value: abnormal spindle assembly during meiosis I

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which assembly of the meiotic spindle is abnormal during the first meiotic nuclear division.

label.value: normal spindle elongation during meiotic metaphase I

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the spindle elongates during metaphase of the first meiotic nuclear division, when elongation is normally paused.

label.value: normal meiotic spindle length during prophase I

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype in which the length of the meiotic spindle is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) during prophase I.

label.value: increased duration of spindle assembly during meiosis I

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the duration of spindle assembly during meiosis I is longer than normal. The total duration of spindle phases I (initial assembly and first stage of elongation) and II (in which elongation normally pauses, and which coincides with metaphase I) is increased due to prolongation of either or both phases.

label.value: decreased protein localization to meiotic spindle during meiosis I

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the localization of a protein to the spindle is decreased during the first meiotic nuclear division.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal protein localization to meiotic spindle during meiosis I

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the localization of a protein to the spindle is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) during the first meiotic nuclear division.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.
